elements.title: Oceanic Steamship Company
elements.contents: ... that the Oceanic Steamship Company (advertisement pictured) beat a rival company in a trans-Pacific race, bought the rival's ships, and added them to its own fleet?

elements.title: Sagittarius Ponderosa

elements.title: Five Bullets
elements.contents: ... that the author of Five Bullets was unaware for a year that Fear and Fury was also being written about the same 1984 shooting, and for the same publishing house?

elements.title: a church in Colorado
elements.contents: ... that a church in Colorado merged with another congregation, was sold, became a nightclub, and then was bought by an offshoot of the merged congregation?

elements.title: prattling pieces
elements.contents: ... that volumes of one writer's journalism were variously described as "prattling pieces", delivering "a snigger a minute", and having a "souffle touch"?

elements.title: Taco Dowler
elements.contents: ... that American football player Taco Dowler is the twin of a football player who was called "Burrito"?

elements.title: Load
elements.contents: ... that the cover artworks for Metallica's Load and Reload were created by mixing blood with semen and urine, respectively?
